Santander, Faes Farma, Espirito Santo: Iberian Equity Preview

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-03-30T04:00:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/santander-faes-farma-espirito-santo-iberian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spanish and Portuguese trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index (IBEX)  dropped 0.2 percent to 10,735.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index (PSI20)  fell 0.2 percent to 7,817.27.  Spanish stocks:  Banco Santander SA (SAN)  : Spain’s biggest lender
purchased 96 percent of Poland’s Bank Zachodni WBK SA for 3.99
billion euros ($5.62 billion) from Allied Irish Banks Plc.
Santander will also buy 50 percent of BZ WBK Asset Management
from Allied Irish for 150 million euros in cash, the Madrid-
based lender said in a statement. Santander shares slipped 1.3
percent to 8.45 euros.  Faes Farma SA (FAE)  : The Spanish drugmaker will start
selling its allergy treatment Bilastina in Spanish pharmacies in
the first week of April. The treatment will be marketed under
the brand Bilaxten, the company said in a regulatory filing. The
shares fell 0.2 percent to 2.80 euros.  Portuguese stocks:  Banco Espirito Santo SA (BES)  : Portugal’s biggest
publicly traded bank by market value said in a presentation it
sold 1.3 billion euros ($1.8 billion) of loans during the first
quarter. The shares dropped 2.3 percent to 3.02 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net . 